  "notes": "Eastern Yiddish (YIVO standard). Unlike Hebrew, Yiddish writes vowels fully (matres lectionis system extended). Written right-to-left. Dagesh distinguishes פּ /p/ vs פ/פֿ /f/, בּ /b/ vs בֿ /v/. Shin with right dot שׁ = /ʃ/, sin with left dot שׂ = /s/. ו = /u/, וו = /v/, י = /j/ or vowel marker, יי = /ɛɪ/.",
